Here's a complete implementation:

### XAML

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding SelectedItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="48,*" ColumnSpacing="12">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}" WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                    <Label Grid.Column="1" Text="{Binding Name}" VerticalOptions="Center" />
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        <CollectionView.EmptyView>
            <Label Text="No items found." HorizontalOptions="Center" VerticalOptions="Center" />
        </CollectionView.EmptyView>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

### ViewModel

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;
    private readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private ObservableCollection<Item> items = new();

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? selectedItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool isRefreshing;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelected()
    {
        if (SelectedItem is null) return;

        await _nav.GoToAsync(nameof(DetailPage), new Dictionary<string, object>
        {
            { "Item", SelectedItem }
        });

        // Clear selection so the same item can be re-selected later
        SelectedItem = null;
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task Refresh()
    {
        try
        {
            var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
            Items = new ObservableCollection<Item>(data);
        }
        finally
        {
            IsRefreshing = false; // Must set false to dismiss the spinner
        }
    }
}
```

### Key bindings explained

| XAML Property | ViewModel Property | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `IsRefreshing` | `IsRefreshing` (bool, TwoWay) | Shows/hides the refresh spinner. **You must set it to `false`** when done. |
| `Command` (RefreshView) | `RefreshCommand` | Fires on pull-to-refresh to reload data. |
| `SelectedItem` | `SelectedItem` (TwoWay) | Tracks the currently selected item. Clear it after navigation. |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` | `ItemSelectedCommand` | Fires when selection changes — triggers navigation. |
| `ItemsSource` | `Items` (ObservableCollection) | Use `ObservableCollection<T>`, never `List<T>`, so the UI updates automatically. |

### Important notes

- **Never use `ViewCell`** in the item template — use `Grid`, `StackLayout`, etc.
- Set `x:DataType` on `DataTemplate` for compiled bindings.
- Always set `IsRefreshing = false` in a `finally` block so the spinner dismisses even on errors.
- Clear `SelectedItem` after navigation so the user can tap the same item again.
